./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:450:### Phase 4: Codex Status, Drafting, and Research
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:454:- Convert Codex status checks, draft preflight, bounded URL/codebase research, timeout handling, and draft error mapping into Effect services.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:470:- `CodexEnvironment` wraps CLI availability, auth file/API key checks, and SDK env creation.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:474:- Use `Schedule` only for safe URL research retry, not for Codex generation.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:496:- Current timeout behavior intentionally logs late Codex completions/failures; replacing it with interruption must preserve that observability or intentionally update tests.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:503:- Migrate the long-running Codex run lifecycle after runtime, storage, and draft services are stable.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:558:- The Codex SDK may require AbortSignal behavior that is not naturally identical to Effect interruption.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:565:- Evaluate whether local Effect AI packages can replace or supplement bespoke Codex SDK structures.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:582:- Map Relay's `RelayCodexEvent` to provider events in a test-only adapter first.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:583:- Evaluate `OpenAiTool.ApplyPatch` and `OpenAiTool.LocalShell` only if Relay chooses to own tool execution beyond the Codex SDK.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:600:- If generated package APIs are unstable, keep Codex SDK as the live provider and retain notes only.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:604:- Generated API surfaces may not match the Codex SDK workflow.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:657:- Use Effect `Config` for process/app-level settings, not as an immediate replacement for project `.relay/project.json`.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:660:- Do not replace `@openai/codex-sdk` or Relay's current Codex event model until a dedicated AI/provider phase.
./docs/backend-effect-v4-upgrade-plan.md:670:- Should future AI/provider work support Anthropic/OpenAI directly, or is Codex SDK the only supported agent backend for now?
